The paper deals with 3D Computer Vision and deep learning, which are both subfields of computer science. The focus is on learning rotation equivariant descriptors, which is a common problem in computer vision and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves end-to-end learning and unsupervised learning, which are topics covered in cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with geometric representations and convolutional neural networks, which are relevant to cs.GR (Graphics). The use of deep learning and neural networks also suggests cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves learning from raw data, which is a topic covered in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
